  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Finance Manager",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>About the role:</strong></u></p>\n<p>Our client is looking for a CPA / CA-qualified finance professional to take ownership of group-level accounting, systems, and process optimization within a dynamic, multinational environment. This role is highly hands-on and strategic, involving close collaboration with senior management, offshore finance teams, and cross-functional stakeholders across the region.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>CPA / CA qualified with 8+ years’ experience, including at least 5 years in commercial finance roles outside of audit.</li>\n  <li>Strong background in group-level accounting for multinationals, including consolidations and financial statement preparation.</li>\n  <li>Proven expertise in accounting systems implementation, process migration to offshore/shared service teams, and governance oversight.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrated ability to design scalable accounting frameworks, streamline reporting, and optimize charts of accounts and workflows.</li>\n  <li>Advanced Excel and analytical skills; Power BI or data visualization tools preferred; strong communication and stakeholder management essential.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead the accounting framework for Singapore-based entities, including system implementation and migration of records.</li>\n  <li>Oversee and collaborate with offshore accounting teams on bookkeeping, consolidations, and statutory reporting.</li>\n  <li>Streamline financial and management reporting processes to enhance group-wide transparency and decision-making.</li>\n  <li>Partner with FP&amp;A and regional finance teams to align accounting systems with business needs and share best practices.</li>\n  <li>Manage finance operations (cash/FX, tax compliance, investor capital calls/distributions) and support strategic transactions such as M&amp;A and restructurings.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 23S1921</p>\n<p>R21100680</p>",
